civicr 0.1.0
  • Reference

Get a specific variant group metadata information

getVariantGroupMetadata.Rd

Retrieve metadata information for a specific variant group from the CIViC DB

getVariantGroupMetadata(id, type)

Arguments

id

Internal CIViC ID of the variant group of interest
type

Type of metadata (comments, suggested_changes, revisions)

Value

An S3 Object of type civic_api containing the content, url, and response

Examples

getVariantGroupMetadata(id = 1, type = "comments")
#> $content
#> list()
#> 
#> $url
#> [1] "https://civicdb.org/api/variant_groups/1/comments"
#> 
#> $response
#> Response [https://civicdb.org/api/variant_groups/1/comments]
#>   Date: 2019-09-03 16:44
#>   Status: 200
#>   Content-Type: application/json; charset=utf-8
#>   Size: 2 B
#> 
#> 
#> attr(,"class")
#> [1] "civic_api"
